WEBVTT

00:01.349 --> 00:03.481
PREVIOUSLY ON "WHITE COLLAR"...

00:03.568 --> 00:04.743
Neal:
I BROKE INTO PETER'S SAFE.

00:04.830 --> 00:06.136
I HAD THE LIST IN MY HAND.

00:06.223 --> 00:07.398
I WAS READY
TO TAKE THE TREASURE AND GO.

00:07.485 --> 00:08.617
THEN WHY DIDN'T YOU?

00:08.704 --> 00:09.661
I HAVE A LIFE HERE.

00:09.748 --> 00:11.011
I RUN ON THIS,

00:11.098 --> 00:13.056
AND NEW YORK
IS JUST A MEMORY FOR ME.

00:13.143 --> 00:14.710
HE STOLE A RAPHAEL!CONJECTURE, YOUR HONOR.

00:14.797 --> 00:16.320
AND I PURSUED.

00:16.407 --> 00:18.105
AND I HAVEN'T FORGOTTEN
ABOUT THE RAPHAEL.OHH!

00:18.192 --> 00:19.976
NEAL CODED HIS LETTERS.

00:20.063 --> 00:21.325
AND WE CRACKED IT.

00:21.412 --> 00:24.067
DON'T KNOW WHAT THEY MEAN YET,
BUT WE WILL.

00:24.154 --> 00:25.851
I'M --
AGENT KRAMER.

00:25.938 --> 00:27.418
HEAD OF THE BUREAU'S
D.C. ART CRIMES UNIT.

00:27.505 --> 00:29.594
SO YOU'RE THE ONE WHO TAUGHT
PETER EVERYTHING HE KNOWS.

00:29.681 --> 00:32.467
I'D SAY THIS MOMENT
WAS INEVITABLE, MR. CAFFREY.

00:32.554 --> 00:34.556
Peter: NEAL'S MY C.I.HE'S ALSO A FRIEND.

00:34.643 --> 00:36.862
YOU THINK ONCE A CON,
ALWAYS A CON?

00:36.949 --> 00:39.604
I THINK YOU HAVE TO PROTECT
YOURSELF WHEN THEY FALL.

00:39.691 --> 00:41.215
YOU HAVE THE TREASURE.

00:41.302 --> 00:42.912
I DIDN'T STEAL IT.YOU SON OF A BITCH!

00:42.999 --> 00:44.435
I DON'T CARE.
YOU HAVEIT.

00:44.522 --> 00:45.610
WHERE IS IT?

00:45.697 --> 00:46.916
IT WAS HERE.

00:47.003 --> 00:48.004
HE ALREADY MOVED IT.

00:48.091 --> 00:49.832
MOZZIE?
OF COURSE IT WAS MOZZIE.

00:49.919 --> 00:51.268
I DIDN'T THINK HE'D MOVE IT
THIS FAST.

00:51.355 --> 00:52.617
WHAT IS IT?

00:52.704 --> 00:54.793
THIS IS A LETTER
FROM THE U.S. PROBATION OFFICE.

00:54.880 --> 00:57.057
"BECAUSE OF YOUR
OUTSTANDING SERVICE,

00:57.144 --> 00:58.710
"INCLUDING RECOVERING
THE TREASURE

00:58.797 --> 01:00.886
"AND CATCHING KELLER,

01:00.973 --> 01:03.715
"THE U.S. PROBATION OFFICE
IS CONVENING A HEARING

01:03.802 --> 01:06.240
TO DISCUSS THE COMMUTATION
OF YOUR SENTENCE."

01:06.327 --> 01:07.458
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

01:07.545 --> 01:09.417
IT MEANS NO ANKLET.

01:09.504 --> 01:10.722
NO NOTHING.

01:10.809 --> 01:14.683
YOU COULD BE A FREE MAN.

01:17.120 --> 01:19.688
Holloman: STATE YOUR NAME
FOR THE RECORD, PLEASE.

01:19.775 --> 01:21.777
NEAL GEORGE CAFFREY.

01:21.864 --> 01:23.648
MR. CAFFREY, DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU'RE SITTING HERE TODAY?

01:23.735 --> 01:25.215
I DO.

01:25.302 --> 01:28.305
THE U.S. ATTORNEY HAS PETITIONED
A RULE 35 MOTION

01:28.392 --> 01:30.351
ON MY BEHALF,
WHICH, IF GRANTED,

01:30.438 --> 01:33.528
WOULD COMMUTE MY SENTENCE AND
SET ABOUT MY OWN RECOGNIZANCE.

01:33.615 --> 01:36.574
IN ESSENCE, YOU WANT TO KNOW
IF I'VE EARNED MY FREEDOM.

01:36.661 --> 01:38.141
YOU'VE DONE
YOUR HOMEWORK.

01:38.228 --> 01:40.361
YES, MA'AM.

01:40.448 --> 01:42.014
YOU'VE ALREADY SERVED TWO YEARS
OF A FOUR-YEAR SENTENCE

01:42.102 --> 01:44.713
UNDER THE SUPERVISION
OF SPECIAL AGENT PETER BURKE.

01:44.800 --> 01:46.584
YES, MA'AM.

01:46.671 --> 01:48.325
WHILE CONFINED
TO A TRACKING ANKLET,

01:48.412 --> 01:50.371
YOU'VE HELPED
AGENT BURKE CLEAR

01:50.458 --> 01:52.503
AN IMPRESSIVE
94% CONVICTION RATE.

01:52.590 --> 01:55.202
WE WORK WELL TOGETHER.

01:55.289 --> 01:57.856
IT WOULD SEEM SO.

01:57.943 --> 01:59.771
THE RECENT ARREST
OF MATTHEW KELLER,

01:59.858 --> 02:01.991
ONE OF THE FBI's TOP 10
MOST WANTED FUGITIVES,

02:02.078 --> 02:03.819
THE RECOVERY
OF A PRICELESS COLLECTION

02:03.906 --> 02:04.994
OF ARTWORK HE STOLE --

02:05.081 --> 02:07.301
YOU ARE THE POSTER BOY
FOR REFORM.

02:07.388 --> 02:09.041
WHO WOULD HAVE THOUGHT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:10.478 --> 02:13.263
YOU CAME INTO THIS LEGAL SYSTEM
AS A CRIMINAL.

02:13.350 --> 02:15.831
THE QUESTION BEFORE THIS BOARD
TODAY IS -- HAVE YOU CHANGED?

02:15.918 --> 02:17.920
I BELIEVE I HAVE.

02:18.007 --> 02:20.183
OVER THE NEXT TWO DAYS,

02:20.270 --> 02:21.619
WE'LL BE INTERVIEWING SOME
OF YOUR CLOSEST ACQUAINTANCES

02:21.706 --> 02:23.143
AND COLLEAGUES.

02:23.230 --> 02:25.145
THEN WE'LL HAVE YOU BACK
TO MAKE A FINAL STATEMENT,

02:25.232 --> 02:26.929
AT WHICH TIME AGENT BURKE

02:27.016 --> 02:28.757
WILL GIVE HIS
SUMMARY RECOMMENDATION.

02:28.844 --> 02:29.975
ANY QUESTIONS?

02:30.062 --> 02:32.239
NO, MA'AM.

02:32.326 --> 02:34.241
BUT MAY I SAY THAT
THE LAST TWO YEARS OF MY LIFE

02:34.328 --> 02:35.720
HAVE BEEN THE BEST --

02:35.807 --> 02:38.201
YOU'LL HAVE TIME FOR ALL THAT
TWO DAYS FROM NOW.

02:38.288 --> 02:39.289
YES, MA'AM.

02:39.376 --> 02:41.161
THIS IS IMPRESSIVE,
MR. CAFFREY.

02:41.248 --> 02:44.773
I HOPE THE REAL YOU LIVES UP
TO WHO YOU ARE ON PAPER.

02:44.860 --> 02:46.949
I HOPE TO EXCEED
YOUR EXPECTATION.

02:52.084 --> 02:53.999
YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

02:58.482 --> 03:00.136
Moz: "FREE TO GO."

03:00.223 --> 03:02.094
QUITE AN INSPIRING
TURN OF PHRASE.

03:02.182 --> 03:04.619
EXCEPT "YOU'RE FREE TO STAY"
MIGHT BE MORE APPROPRIATE.

03:04.706 --> 03:06.273
HOW'S IT LOOKING?

03:06.360 --> 03:07.796
OH, FLIP A COIN.
[ SIGHS ]

03:07.883 --> 03:10.842
REGARDLESS OF WHAT
THE COMMITTEE DECIDES,

03:10.929 --> 03:13.584
THIS IS MY HOME NOW.

03:13.671 --> 03:16.674
AND I AM RIGHT
BESIDE YOU.

03:16.761 --> 03:19.373
MAKE A BRAND-NEW START
OF IT IN OLD NEW YORK.

03:19.460 --> 03:20.809
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

03:22.724 --> 03:24.595
WELL, WHEN YOU MAKE
THAT BRAND-NEW START,

03:24.682 --> 03:25.683
I'VE GOT A SURPRISE.

03:25.770 --> 03:28.033
WHAT KIND OF SURPRISE?OH, A HUGE ONE.

03:28.120 --> 03:30.645
MAKES CANIS MAJORIS
LOOK LIKE A NIGHT LIGHT.

03:30.732 --> 03:32.386
BUT I WILL SAY NO MORE.

03:32.473 --> 03:33.648
I'LL ASK NO MORE.

03:33.735 --> 03:36.346
OH.

03:36.433 --> 03:37.956
THERE SEEMS TO BE
SOMEONE MISSING

03:38.043 --> 03:39.436
FROM YOUR COMMUTATION
WITNESS LIST.

03:39.523 --> 03:41.351
YEAH, SORRY ABOUT THAT,

03:41.438 --> 03:43.223
BUT HAVING A KNOWN FELON
SPEAK FOR ME

03:43.310 --> 03:45.355
DOESN'T QUALIFY
AS A GOOD CHARACTER REFERENCE.

03:45.442 --> 03:47.227
I AM A FELON,
BUT I'M NOT KNOWN--

03:47.314 --> 03:49.054
AT LEAST IN
BUREAUCRATIC CIRCLES.

03:49.141 --> 03:50.578
I STAND CORRECTED.

03:50.665 --> 03:52.667
BUT I'VE ALREADY GOT PLENTY
OF PEOPLE ON MY SIDE.

03:52.754 --> 03:55.322
ELIZABETH, JUNE...SARA.

03:55.409 --> 03:57.019
REALLY?
YEAH.

03:57.106 --> 03:59.804
GOOD.
WHAT ABOUT THE DEMI-SUITS?

03:59.891 --> 04:02.503
MM. JONES AND DIANA?
WILD CARDS.

04:02.590 --> 04:04.896
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, AND THE SUIT HIMSELF?

04:04.983 --> 04:07.377
WELL, CONSIDERING EVERYTHING
THAT'S HAPPENED --

04:07.464 --> 04:09.336
WITH THE TREASURE,
WITH KELLER --

04:09.423 --> 04:10.859
PETER COULD GO
EITHER WAY.

04:10.946 --> 04:12.121
THINK HE'S DECIDED?

04:12.208 --> 04:14.819
I DON'T KNOW.

04:14.906 --> 04:16.908
OH, HOLD ON.

04:16.995 --> 04:19.737
AGENT KRAMER, THE D.C.
ART CRIMES GRAND-PÃ¨RE --

04:19.824 --> 04:21.304
HE'S SPEAKING?

04:21.391 --> 04:22.914
KRAMER WAS SUPPOSED TO SUBMIT
A WRITTEN REPORT

04:23.001 --> 04:25.177
ON BEHALF OF THE BUREAU.

04:25.265 --> 04:27.441
IF HE'S SPEAKING IN PERSON,
THAT'S MORE THAN A FORMALITY.

04:27.528 --> 04:29.225
WELL, WHAT DOES THAT DO
TO YOUR CHANCES?

04:29.312 --> 04:32.576
WELL, I CAN'T IMAGINE
IT IMPROVES THEM.

04:32.663 --> 04:35.318
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WORST-CASE SCENARIO, HE SAYS NO,

04:35.405 --> 04:37.538
AND I STAY ON THE ANKLET
WITH PETER.

04:37.625 --> 04:40.410
WELL, BEHIND EVERY
WORST-CASE SCENARIO,

04:40.497 --> 04:42.978
THERE'S A WORSE
WORST-CASE SCENARIO.

04:43.065 --> 04:44.284
ISN'T THERE A CHILD

04:44.371 --> 04:45.589
WHOSE BALLOON YOU NEED
TO POP SOMEWHERE?

04:45.676 --> 04:48.331
OH. YEAH. NEGATIVITY --
FORCE OF HABIT.

04:48.418 --> 04:50.638
I'M...SURE
IT DOESN'T MEAN ANYTHING.

04:50.725 --> 04:52.944
YEAH. NOTHING.

04:53.031 --> 04:55.643
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

04:55.730 --> 04:57.122
HEY.
HEY.

04:57.209 --> 04:58.341
COME ON IN.

04:58.428 --> 04:59.560
SMELLS GOOD IN HERE.

04:59.647 --> 05:01.083
YEAH.
EL'S BEEN BAKING.

05:08.090 --> 05:10.222
A COMMUTATION CAKE.

05:10.310 --> 05:12.964
YEAH, I TOLD HER
IT WAS A LITTLE PREMATURE.

05:13.051 --> 05:14.705
HEY, HONEY.
I GOT THAT OTHER CAKE.

05:14.792 --> 05:16.185
[ LAUGHS ]
WAIT TILL YOU SEE IT.

05:16.272 --> 05:17.447
HEY.

05:17.534 --> 05:19.797
OH. HEY!OH. "HANG IN THERE."

05:19.884 --> 05:21.886
LITTLE CAT
WITH AN ANKLET.

05:21.973 --> 05:23.061
OH.
[ LAUGHS ]

05:23.148 --> 05:24.193
CONSOLATION CAKE.AH.

05:24.280 --> 05:26.630
RUM?
LOTS OF RUM.

05:26.717 --> 05:27.762
THAT'LL BE GOOD.YEAH.YES.

05:27.849 --> 05:29.198
WELL,
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

05:29.285 --> 05:30.373
I'M ACTUALLY VOTING
FOR CAKE NUMBER ONE.

05:30.460 --> 05:31.635
I APPRECIATE THAT.

05:31.722 --> 05:32.593
YOU GUYS TALK.

05:36.423 --> 05:38.250
SO, HAVE YOU DECIDED?

05:38.338 --> 05:40.949
WHAT I'M GONNA SAY?
HONESTLY...

05:41.036 --> 05:42.777
NO. I HAVEN'T.

05:42.864 --> 05:46.171
SO, WHAT'S SO IMPORTANT
YOU COULDN'T CALL?

05:46.258 --> 05:49.523
WHY IS KRAMER SPEAKING
AT MY HEARING?

05:49.610 --> 05:52.003
DON'T LET THAT
PUT YOU ON EDGE.

05:52.090 --> 05:54.528
PETER, I'M STARING
AT TWO CAKES HERE.

05:54.615 --> 05:56.268
ONE CELEBRATES MY FATE,

05:56.356 --> 05:58.401
THE OTHER SEALS IT --
I AM ON EDGE. WHY IS HE HERE?

05:58.488 --> 06:00.534
I DON'T KNOW.
FOR WHATEVER REASON,

06:00.621 --> 06:02.840
KRAMER HAS DECIDED TO KEEP ME
OUT OF THE LOOP ON THIS.

06:02.927 --> 06:05.626
HE'S KEEPING YOUOUT?
YEAH.

06:05.713 --> 06:06.844
BUT I'VE GOT
AN INSIDE MAN.

06:08.455 --> 06:10.282
HOW'D IT GO
WITH KRAMER?

06:10.370 --> 06:12.850
HE HAD ME DIGGING THROUGH FILES
TILL 3:00 A.M.

06:12.937 --> 06:14.939
WHAT'S
HE TRYING TO PROVE?

06:15.026 --> 06:16.114
I DON'T KNOW.

06:16.201 --> 06:17.246
WHEN HE TALKS ABOUT CAFFREY,

06:17.333 --> 06:18.465
HE TALKS ABOUT HIM
IN GLOWING TERMS.

06:18.552 --> 06:20.118
I NOTICED THAT.

06:20.205 --> 06:22.904
HE SEEMS TO RESPECT THE HELL
OUT OF HIM.

06:22.991 --> 06:24.732
BUT HE'S DIGGING
INTO THE CODED LETTERS

06:24.819 --> 06:26.298
NEAL SENT KATE
FROM PRISON.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.257
AND NOW THAT KRAMER'S
CRACKED THE CODE,

06:28.344 --> 06:29.998
HE'S CONVINCED
HE'LL FIND SOMETHING.

06:30.085 --> 06:33.001
YEAH. BUT WHAT?

06:43.620 --> 06:46.449
HA HA! PETEY!

06:46.536 --> 06:47.885
HOW ARE YOU?

06:47.972 --> 06:49.452
I'M GOOD.

06:49.539 --> 06:52.020
OH. IT'S AN INTERESTING PLACE
TO SET UP SHOP.

06:52.107 --> 06:54.805
YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'T BE MORE
COMFORTABLE IN AN OFFICE?

06:54.892 --> 06:57.286
WELL, I DON'T WANT TO INTRUDE
ON SOMEONE ELSE'S HOUSE.

06:57.373 --> 06:58.896
AND THIS LETS ME
SPREAD OUT.

06:58.983 --> 07:01.856
AND THIS ISTHE ROOM
WHERE WE FIND THE TRUTH.

07:01.943 --> 07:04.075
THAT'S HOW
IT'S SUPPOSED TO WORK.

07:04.162 --> 07:05.686
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:05.773 --> 07:08.645
I NEED TO STRETCH
MY LEGS.

07:08.732 --> 07:12.083
WALK WITH ME.

07:12.170 --> 07:14.564
YOU'VE GOT SOMETHING
ON YOUR MIND?

07:14.651 --> 07:17.262
YOU'RE STILL PULLING
NEAL'S CASEWORK.

07:17.349 --> 07:19.961
IS THERE SOMETHING GOING ON
I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?

07:20.048 --> 07:22.659
MATTER OF FACT, THERE IS.
I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU, PETE.

07:22.746 --> 07:24.313
YOU'RE WORRIED?

07:24.400 --> 07:28.143
YEAH. THE MUSIC BOX,
GARRETT FOWLER, THE U-BOAT.

07:28.230 --> 07:31.059
THESE 515s READ MORE LIKE
PULP FICTION

07:31.146 --> 07:32.669
THAN CASE SUMMARIES.

07:32.756 --> 07:34.236
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

07:34.323 --> 07:36.586
WELL, YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M SAYING.

07:36.673 --> 07:38.066
YOU'RE COVERING FOR HIM.

07:40.329 --> 07:42.026
NO, YOU'RE NOT?

07:42.113 --> 07:44.289
IT'S COMPLICATED.

07:44.376 --> 07:47.336
MM. IF ANYONE GETS IT,
I DO.

07:47.423 --> 07:49.033
HE'S YOUR FRIEND.

07:49.120 --> 07:50.557
HE IS, PHIL.

07:50.644 --> 07:53.124
AND I WANT TO MAKE SURE
HE'S NOT GONNA HURT YOU.

07:53.211 --> 07:55.518
YOU WANT HIM
BACK BEHIND BARS?

07:55.605 --> 07:57.868
OH, NO, PETE.

07:57.955 --> 07:59.827
HE'S MUCH TOO VALUABLE
FOR THAT.

07:59.914 --> 08:01.219
MEANING?

08:01.306 --> 08:04.179
I WANT NEAL WORKING FOR ME.
IN D.C.

08:28.899 --> 08:31.641
WHEN DID YOU FIRST MEET
NEAL CAFFREY?

08:31.728 --> 08:33.730
THE DAY HE WAS RELEASED
FROM PRISON.

08:33.817 --> 08:38.256
THEY HAD SENT HIM TO THIS
HORRIBLE LITTLE FLEABAG MOTEL.

08:38.343 --> 08:41.129
AND YOU HAD NO QUALMS ABOUT
TAKING IN A CONVICTED FELON?

08:41.216 --> 08:43.000
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

08:43.087 --> 08:44.915
NOT NEAL.

08:45.002 --> 08:48.353
YOU SEE,
AFTER MY HUSBAND PASSED,

08:48.440 --> 08:52.444
I...I WAS LIVING IN THIS BIG,
EMPTY HOUSE.

08:52.532 --> 08:56.536
AND...NEAL CHANGED
ALL OF THAT.

08:58.538 --> 09:00.322
I THINK OF HIM
AS A BLESSING.

09:00.409 --> 09:04.326
BYRON AND I ALWAYS
WANTED A SON.

09:06.154 --> 09:09.505
[ Voice breaking ]
I WISH HE WAS STILL ALIVE...

09:09.592 --> 09:13.291
SO THAT HE COULD
FINALLY MEET HIM.

09:13.378 --> 09:18.166
MISS ELLINGTON,
IN YOUR OPINION,

09:18.253 --> 09:21.517
DOES NEAL CAFFREY DESERVE
FOR HIS SENTENCE TO BE COMMUTED?

09:21.604 --> 09:23.127
OF COURSE.

09:23.214 --> 09:25.303
YES.

09:25.390 --> 09:28.785
AND YOU MUST
LET HIM GO FREE.

09:34.225 --> 09:36.793
[ HORNS HONKING ]

09:36.880 --> 09:39.622
HOW'D IT GO?

09:39.709 --> 09:41.885
I NAILEDIT.

09:41.972 --> 09:43.713
NICE.

09:50.677 --> 09:53.984
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

09:54.071 --> 09:55.551
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

09:55.638 --> 09:57.335
I'M THINKING WE NEED
A THIRD CAKE.

09:57.422 --> 09:58.641
ONE WITH A FILE IN IT?

09:58.728 --> 10:00.251
ONE THAT SAYS
"BON VOYAGE."

10:00.338 --> 10:02.384
KRAMER DOESN'T
WANT TO PUT NEAL AWAY.

10:02.471 --> 10:04.473
HE WANTS TO KEEP HIM
FOR HIMSELF IN D.C.

10:04.560 --> 10:05.692
HE'D TAKE NEAL AWAY
FROM YOU?

10:05.779 --> 10:08.782
FOR MY OWN GOOD,
BUT THAT'S NOT...

10:08.869 --> 10:11.219
WHAT IS IT?

10:11.306 --> 10:13.134
ONE NIGHT,
FROM SUNSET TO SUNRISE,

10:13.221 --> 10:14.614
I GAVE NEAL FULL IMMUNITY

10:14.701 --> 10:16.572
TO TELL ME EVERYTHING
HE'D EVER DONE.

10:16.659 --> 10:18.008
WOW. AND HE DID?

10:18.095 --> 10:19.488
OH, BOY, HE DID.

10:19.575 --> 10:21.185
BUT HE HAS FULL IMMUNITY.

10:21.272 --> 10:23.579
IT WAS MYIMMUNITY,
NOT THE BUREAU'S.

10:23.666 --> 10:25.712
IF KRAMER DIGS UP
THESE THINGS --

10:25.799 --> 10:27.365
NEAL COULD GET
THE MAXIMUM.

10:27.452 --> 10:29.106
FORGET D.C.
FORGET THE ANKLET.

10:29.193 --> 10:30.455
HE COULD GO BACK
TO PRISON.

10:30.542 --> 10:33.154
FOR A LONG, LONG TIME.

10:33.241 --> 10:34.372
HAVE YOU TOLD HIM?

10:34.459 --> 10:35.417
NO.
HON...

10:35.504 --> 10:36.940
I CAN'T.

10:37.027 --> 10:40.074
WHEN NEAL'S THREATENED,
HE GETS IN EVEN MORE TROUBLE.

10:41.684 --> 10:44.121
TALK TO KRAMER.
HE'S YOUR FRIEND.

10:44.208 --> 10:47.124
HE DOESN'T KNOW
THE PANDORA'S BOX HE'S OPENING.

10:57.178 --> 10:58.745
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

10:58.832 --> 11:00.007
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:05.839 --> 11:07.188
HEY.

11:07.275 --> 11:08.624
HEY.

11:08.711 --> 11:10.104
I'M JUST SKIMMING
MONDAY'S CASELOAD,

11:10.191 --> 11:11.845
TRYING TO GET
A HEAD START.

11:11.932 --> 11:14.369
THIS GRABOWSKA INSURANCE FRAUD
LOOKS PRETTY PROMISING.

11:14.456 --> 11:16.458
I LIKE THAT ATTITUDE.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.735
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:32.822 --> 11:34.606
I WONDERED HOW LONG
IT WOULD BE

11:34.694 --> 11:36.478
BEFORE YOU CAME BACK
TO SEE ME.

11:36.565 --> 11:38.785
PHILIP.
WE NEED TO TALK.

11:38.872 --> 11:40.308
I SUPPOSE WE DO.

11:40.395 --> 11:42.789
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
ON NEAL?

11:42.876 --> 11:45.400
OH, THAT'S NOT
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

11:46.749 --> 11:48.229
NEAL NEEDS BOUNDARIES.

11:48.316 --> 11:49.709
I KNOW THAT.

11:49.796 --> 11:52.581
YOU DO?

11:52.668 --> 11:55.715
I TOLD YOU ABOUT MYC.I.
MY "NEAL."

11:55.802 --> 11:57.238
YEAH.
YOU WERE CLOSE.

11:57.325 --> 12:00.371
OH, WE WERE MORE THAN CLOSE.
HE WAS LIKE A SON.

12:00.458 --> 12:02.852
HELL, I THOUGHT I'D BROUGHT HIM
ALL THE WAY AROUND,

12:02.939 --> 12:05.028
BUT HE COULDN'T CHANGE
WHO HE WAS.

12:05.115 --> 12:07.988
WELL, YOU KNOW, JUST BECAUSE
YOU SLAPPED CUFFS ON YOUR C.I.

12:08.075 --> 12:11.992
DOESN'T MEAN THAT I'LL HAVE TO
DO THE SAME TO NEAL.

12:12.079 --> 12:15.212
YOU KNOW THE STORY
OF THE FROG AND THE SCORPION?

12:15.299 --> 12:16.779
MM-HMM.

12:16.866 --> 12:20.391
NEAL'S THE SCORPION.

12:20.478 --> 12:24.134
HE CAN'T HELP WHO HE IS.
BUT HE WILL STING YOU.

12:24.221 --> 12:25.701
AND YOU'LL BOTH DROWN.

12:25.788 --> 12:27.877
IN D.C.,
I CAN KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.

12:27.964 --> 12:30.358
[ Chuckling ]
WHAT HAPPENS IN TWO YEARS,

12:30.445 --> 12:32.664
WHEN HE'S A FREE MAN?

12:32.752 --> 12:34.666
WHO'S TO SAY HE WILL BE?

12:34.754 --> 12:36.277
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE AFTER.

12:36.364 --> 12:38.366
YOU WANT TO USE
WHATEVER YOU FIND

12:38.453 --> 12:40.498
TO EXTEND
HIS SENTENCE INDEFINITELY.

12:40.585 --> 12:41.891
IT'S BEST
FOR ALL CONCERNED.

12:41.978 --> 12:43.414
PHIL --

12:43.501 --> 12:45.068
HE GETS TO DO
WHAT HE'S SO DAMN GOOD AT,

12:45.155 --> 12:48.158
AND HE WON'T END UP
BEING LOCKED AWAY OR WORSE.

12:48.245 --> 12:49.986
I DON'T THINK
HE SHOULD GO FREE.

12:50.073 --> 12:51.683
YOU MEAN THAT?

12:51.771 --> 12:53.033
I DO.

12:53.120 --> 12:55.383
UNTIL THIS MOMENT,
I DIDN'T, BUT NO.

12:55.470 --> 12:56.732
Neal: SARA.

12:56.819 --> 12:58.690
NEAL SHOULD NOT GO FREE.

12:58.778 --> 13:02.085
IN TWO YEARS TIME,
WHEN HIS SENTENCE ISOVER,

13:02.172 --> 13:04.566
HE'S EARNED THAT RIGHT
TO DECIDE HIS OWN LIFE.

13:04.653 --> 13:06.568
PETER...

13:06.655 --> 13:11.399
AND UNTIL THEN,
NEAL'S STAYING HERE, WITH ME.

13:14.184 --> 13:18.232
Sara: KRAMER IS
GOING TO SUBPOENA MY FILES?

13:18.319 --> 13:20.364
THAT MEANS I WAS CLOSE
TO THE RAPHAEL.

13:20.451 --> 13:22.018
YES.

13:22.105 --> 13:23.324
I knew it!
You stole it!

13:23.411 --> 13:24.586
MM, YOU CAUGHT ME.

13:24.673 --> 13:25.805
NEAL!

13:25.892 --> 13:27.589
THIS IS SO GREAT!

13:27.676 --> 13:29.330
I'VE SPENT YEARS
LOOKING FOR THAT PAINTING.

13:29.417 --> 13:30.592
HOW CLOSE WAS I?

13:30.679 --> 13:32.724
KRAMER CRACKED
A CODED LETTER

13:32.812 --> 13:34.683
THAT I WROTE IN PRISON
THAT INCLUDES A PARTIAL ADDRESS

13:34.770 --> 13:35.945
OF WHERE I HID IT.

13:36.032 --> 13:37.555
SO YOU THINK I HAVE
THE OTHER PART?

13:37.642 --> 13:38.687
I KNOWYOU DO.

13:38.774 --> 13:40.907
OH, MY GOD.
I WAS SOCLOSE.

13:40.994 --> 13:42.909
YES, YOU WERE.
MM.

13:42.996 --> 13:45.476
WELL, WE ALREADY PAID OUT
THAT CLAIM YEARS AGO.

13:45.563 --> 13:47.391
YOUOWE STERLING BOSCH$15 MILLION.

13:47.478 --> 13:48.697
Shh, shh!

13:48.784 --> 13:51.047
IF I STAY OUT OF PRISON,
I WILL WORK IT OFF.

13:51.134 --> 13:54.007
SO, A CODED ADDRESS
IN A PRISON LETTER --

13:54.094 --> 13:55.965
THAT SEEMS KIND OF CHANCY.

13:56.052 --> 13:57.271
OH, I LEFT OFF
THE ZIP CODE.

13:57.358 --> 13:58.794
AND THE ADDRESS
IS ON MAIN STREET.

13:58.881 --> 14:00.404
YOU KNOW HOW MANY MAIN STREETS
THERE ARE?

14:00.491 --> 14:01.666
PROBABLY THOUSANDS.

14:01.753 --> 14:04.017
19,364 -- AT THE TIME.

14:04.104 --> 14:05.888
SO THE ADDRESS KRAMER FOUND
MEANS NOTHING.

14:05.975 --> 14:07.847
UNLESS HE GETS HIS HANDS
ON THAT ZIP CODE.

14:07.934 --> 14:10.066
IS THIS
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR?

14:10.153 --> 14:12.373
YES, IT IS.

14:12.460 --> 14:14.244
ROOSEVELT ISLAND?

14:14.331 --> 14:16.420
I FOUND THIS DIGGING THROUGH
A BOOZY COURIER'S TRASH.

14:16.507 --> 14:18.205
I KNEW I SHOULDN'T HAVE
GIVEN UP THIS LEAD.

14:18.292 --> 14:19.728
IS THIS THE ONLY COPY?

14:19.815 --> 14:22.035
NO. WE KEEP ELECTRONIC COPIES
OF EVERYTHING ON THE SERVER.

14:22.122 --> 14:23.645
SO I CAN'T
JUST THROW THIS ONE AWAY.

14:23.732 --> 14:25.908
NO.

14:25.995 --> 14:28.128
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

14:29.346 --> 14:31.653
AND I'VE BEEN LOCKED OUT.

14:31.740 --> 14:33.133
Man: EXCUSE ME.
CAN I HELP YOU OUT, SIR?

14:33.220 --> 14:35.396
Man #2: WE'RE HERE
TO SERVE A SUBPOENA.

14:35.483 --> 14:36.788
WE NEED
ALL THE FILES RELATED

14:36.876 --> 14:38.312
TO RAPHAEL'S SAINT GEORGE AND THE DRAGON.FBI.

14:38.399 --> 14:39.966
YEAH.[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

14:40.053 --> 14:42.142
[ SIGHS ]
STERLING BOSCH.

14:42.229 --> 14:43.534
THIS IS SARA ELLIS
SPEAKING.

14:43.621 --> 14:46.407
KRAMER: Ms. Ellis.
Special Agent Kramer, FBI.

14:46.494 --> 14:50.411
AGENT KRAMER!
WHAT CAN I DO TO HELP YOU, SIR?

14:50.498 --> 14:52.456
MY AGENTS ARE SERVING A SUBPOENA
AT YOUR OFFICE

14:52.543 --> 14:54.023
FOR ALL THE FILES RELATED

14:54.110 --> 14:56.025
TO RAPHAEL'S SAINT GEORGE AND THE DRAGON.

14:56.112 --> 14:57.853
[ BEEP ]

14:57.940 --> 14:58.985
WHAT THE HELL AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO?

14:59.072 --> 15:00.334
JUST BUY ME SOME TIME.

15:02.031 --> 15:04.033
WELL, SIR,
YOU MUST HAVE HEARD.

15:04.120 --> 15:05.208
HEARD WHAT?

15:05.295 --> 15:07.080
WE RECOVERED THE PAINTING
THIS MORNING.

15:07.167 --> 15:09.343
YOU RECOVERED THE RAPHAEL
THIS MORNING?

15:09.430 --> 15:11.084
I WAS TOLD TO KEEP IT
UNDER WRAPS

15:11.171 --> 15:13.042
AS WE'RE STILL
WORKING OUT THE DETAILS.

15:13.129 --> 15:14.565
WELL,
WHERE'S THE PAINTING NOW?

15:14.652 --> 15:17.307
WITH OUR AUTHENTICATOR.Good.

15:17.394 --> 15:19.266
I'LL BE THERE MYSELF TO TAKE
POSSESSION OF THE PAINTING

15:19.353 --> 15:20.920
BY END OF BUSINESS TODAY.

15:21.007 --> 15:23.096
And I hope
you're telling me the truth.

15:23.183 --> 15:26.577
BECAUSE IF IT'S NOT THERE
BY 6:00,

15:26.664 --> 15:28.928
I'LL BE CHARGING YOU
WITH OBSTRUCTION OF JUSTICE.

15:29.015 --> 15:31.104
YES, SIR.

15:31.191 --> 15:34.150
I BOUGHT YOU SIX HOURS.

15:34.237 --> 15:35.804
IF THAT PAINTING ISN'T IN MY
HANDS BY THE END OF THE DAY --

15:35.891 --> 15:37.545
IT WILL BE.

15:37.632 --> 15:38.720
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

15:45.335 --> 15:48.338
Holloman: HAS YOUR PERSONAL
RELATIONSHIP WITH MR. CAFFREY

15:48.425 --> 15:49.644
INFLUENCED
YOUR TESTIMONY TODAY?

15:49.731 --> 15:51.167
OH, YES.
MOST DEFINITELY.

15:52.908 --> 15:54.823
THIS ISN'T THE FIRST TIME

15:54.910 --> 15:58.044
YOU'VE TESTIFIED
REGARDING MR. CAFFREY, IS IT?NO.

15:58.131 --> 16:00.481
SIX YEARS AGO,
I TESTIFIED AGAINST HIM.

16:00.568 --> 16:02.744
YES. AT THE TRIAL WHERE HE WAS
CONVICTED OF FORGERY?

16:02.831 --> 16:04.137
YES.

16:04.224 --> 16:05.747
AND I WENT AFTER HIM
WITH EVERYTHING I HAD.

16:05.834 --> 16:08.402
I CALLED HIM A LIAR
AND A THIEF

16:08.489 --> 16:11.971
AND PROBABLY A SOCIOPATH,
AND I MEANT EVERY WORD OF IT.

16:12.058 --> 16:14.321
SO, WHAT CHANGED?

16:14.408 --> 16:16.236
NEAL DID.

16:16.323 --> 16:17.846
PETER: Neal?
Where are you?

16:17.933 --> 16:19.239
YOU KNOW WHERE I AM.

16:19.326 --> 16:20.936
YOU'RE AT THE
ROOSEVELT ISLAND TRAM.

16:21.023 --> 16:22.416
YOU'RE AT THE EDGE
OF YOUR RADIUS.

16:22.503 --> 16:25.114
KRAMER IS GOING AFTER
THE RAPHAEL.

16:25.201 --> 16:27.508
[ SIGHS ]

16:27.595 --> 16:29.727
YOU'LL RECALL
A NIGHT NOT LONG AGO

16:29.814 --> 16:30.641
WHEN YOU SAID
I HAD IMMUNITY?

16:30.728 --> 16:32.165
I REMEMBER, NEAL.

16:32.252 --> 16:34.645
YOU'LL RECALL THAT I SAID
DON'T DO ANYTHING STUPID.

16:34.732 --> 16:37.213
SEVEN YEARS AGO,
I DID SOMETHING STUPID.

16:37.300 --> 16:39.607
KRAMER'S GOING AFTER
THE OLD NEAL CAFFREY.

16:39.694 --> 16:41.391
I need more
than two miles today.

16:41.478 --> 16:43.654
DAMN IT, NEAL, YOU'RE PLAYING
RIGHT INTO KRAMER'S HANDS.

16:43.741 --> 16:44.960
YOU GET CAUGHT,

16:45.047 --> 16:46.266
HE'S GOT YOU ON POSSESSION
OF STOLEN GOODS.

16:46.353 --> 16:48.485
WITH YOUR PRIOR,
THAT'S 25 YEARS.

16:48.572 --> 16:50.270
I CAN'T UNDO
WHAT'S ALREADY BEEN DONE.

16:50.357 --> 16:53.186
BUT I CAN GET BACK
WHAT'S NOT MINE.

16:53.273 --> 16:55.579
I GOT TO GO.

16:55.666 --> 16:58.017
PETER, PLEASE,
EXTEND MY RADIUS.

16:58.104 --> 16:59.235
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

16:59.322 --> 17:01.629
TO OPEN A DOOR
I DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE TO OPEN.

17:04.153 --> 17:05.981
NEAL? NEAL!

17:06.068 --> 17:09.028
[ BEEP ]

17:19.516 --> 17:20.996
COME ON, PETER.

17:24.608 --> 17:27.350
[ DIALING ]

17:27.437 --> 17:29.135
MAN: Electronic Monitoring
Compliance Unit.

17:29.222 --> 17:31.528
THIS IS BURKE, FBI.

17:40.146 --> 17:41.756
COME ON.

17:44.454 --> 17:48.502
THANK YOU, BUDDY.

17:48.589 --> 17:51.983
[ DIALING ]

17:52.071 --> 17:55.422
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

17:55.509 --> 17:56.727
[ BEEP ]

17:56.814 --> 17:58.599
I DON'T RECOGNIZE
THIS NUMBER.

17:58.686 --> 18:02.081
SILENT RUNNING, MOZ.
KRAMER'S AFTER THE RAPHAEL.

18:02.168 --> 18:03.343
Neal, where are you?

18:03.430 --> 18:05.519
ON A TRAM HEADED
FOR ROOSEVELT ISLAND.

18:05.606 --> 18:07.651
REALLY?
ROOSEVELT ISLAND? WHY?

18:07.738 --> 18:09.000
I'LL EXPLAIN LATER.

18:09.088 --> 18:11.133
RIGHT NOW I NEED YOU
TO FIND US TRANSPORTATION.

18:11.220 --> 18:13.135
I MAY NEED YOUR HELP
GETTING BACK.

18:13.222 --> 18:15.703
BYE.

18:19.533 --> 18:21.448
[ BEEPING ]

18:21.535 --> 18:24.233
[ Ringing ]

18:24.320 --> 18:26.670
IT'S NEAL.

18:27.976 --> 18:30.065
[ BUZZER ]

18:40.945 --> 18:42.512
NEAL.

18:42.599 --> 18:45.167
HELEN.

18:45.254 --> 18:47.865
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
SINCE --

18:47.952 --> 18:50.912
SINCE THE DAY
I RAN AWAY.

18:53.044 --> 18:54.872
THIS IS NICE.
MM!

18:54.959 --> 18:57.527
STILL LIVING BY THE RIVER,
I SEE.

18:57.614 --> 19:00.574
IT'S BECOME MY HOME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:02.619 --> 19:05.361
WOW.

19:05.448 --> 19:07.407
IT'S BEEN
A COLD SPRING,

19:07.494 --> 19:09.235
BUT THE HYDRANGEA
ARE COMING BACK.

19:11.280 --> 19:13.413
IS IT HERE?

19:13.500 --> 19:14.849
IT IS.

19:14.936 --> 19:16.242
HOW MUCH TIME
DO YOU HAVE?

19:16.329 --> 19:18.069
MAYBE 10 MINUTES.

19:18.157 --> 19:20.855
[ SIGHS ] THEN LET'S MAKE
THE MOST OF IT.

19:24.250 --> 19:27.470
JONES, CAN YOU PINPOINT WHERE
CAFFREY IS ON ROOSEVELT ISLAND?

19:27.557 --> 19:30.125
YEAH. LOOKS LIKE
HE'S AT 4221 MAIN STREET.

19:30.212 --> 19:31.909
ON MY WAY.

19:31.996 --> 19:33.737
YOU LOOK GOOD.
AH.

19:33.824 --> 19:34.869
THE SAME.

19:34.956 --> 19:36.349
OH, PLEASE.

19:36.436 --> 19:38.916
IT'S BEEN NEARLY
A DECADE AND A HALF.

19:39.003 --> 19:41.528
YEAH, IT WAS
MY 18th BIRTHDAY.

19:41.615 --> 19:43.660
YEAH, I KIND OF RUINED
THATONE FOR YOU.

19:43.747 --> 19:45.009
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:45.096 --> 19:47.621
IT WAS A HELL OF A THING
FOR A KID TO HEAR.

19:57.848 --> 20:00.155
I SAVED THIS FOR YOU.

20:02.940 --> 20:05.769
YOU AND YOUR FATHER.OH, MY GOD.

20:05.856 --> 20:10.165
YOU STILL HAVE HIS EYES.

20:12.689 --> 20:13.821
TRUTH.

20:15.344 --> 20:18.173
DO YOU HATE ME
FOR TELLING YOU WHAT I DID?

20:18.260 --> 20:20.654
NO.

20:20.741 --> 20:23.004
NO, MY MOM TOLD ME
HE WAS DEAD.

20:23.091 --> 20:25.485
SAID HE DIED A HERO,
BUT YOU TOLD ME THE TRUTH.

20:25.572 --> 20:29.271
HE WAS A DIRTY COP...

20:29.358 --> 20:30.838
AND HE'S NOT DEAD.

20:30.925 --> 20:33.580
YOU WERE GONNA GO
AND JOIN THE FORCE.

20:33.667 --> 20:35.451
I TOLD YOUR MOTHER,

20:35.538 --> 20:38.454
"THE MOMENT HE SETS FOOT
IN THE POLICE ACADEMY,

20:38.541 --> 20:40.239
HE'S GONNA
GET AN EARFUL."

20:42.153 --> 20:43.372
TRUTH.

20:45.244 --> 20:47.985
WAS MY FATHER
ALWAYS CORRUPT?

20:48.072 --> 20:52.294
WE MET WHEN WE BECAME PARTNERS
AS FIRST-YEAR DETECTIVES.

20:52.381 --> 20:56.080
HE WAS THE BEST...
THEN.

20:56.167 --> 20:58.518
THE EVIL CAME AFTER.

21:00.520 --> 21:02.348
BUT THAT'S NOT WHY
YOU'RE HERE.

21:03.740 --> 21:04.698
NO.

21:08.876 --> 21:11.270
4221 MAIN STREET.

21:11.357 --> 21:12.358
IT'S A HIGH-RISE.

21:12.445 --> 21:13.663
YEAH, I RAN
ALL THE TENANTS.

21:13.750 --> 21:15.578
The person in 14-E's
been flagged.

21:15.665 --> 21:16.623
FLAGGED BY WHOM?

21:16.710 --> 21:18.538
THE MARSHALS.

21:18.625 --> 21:20.409
E. Parker's
in witness protection.

21:20.496 --> 21:22.759
THANKS, JONES.

21:25.066 --> 21:29.026
HERE IT IS. KEPT IT SAFE.
DIDN'T OPEN IT.

21:29.113 --> 21:31.942
IT'S POSTMARKED THE DAY
BEFORE YOU WERE ARRESTED.

21:32.029 --> 21:33.379
YEAH.

21:33.466 --> 21:36.773
KATE NEVER CAME
TO GET IT?

21:36.860 --> 21:38.732
THE PRETTY GIRL
WITH THE DARK HAIR.
YEAH.

21:38.819 --> 21:40.995
SHE DID.
ALMOST FIVE YEARS AGO NOW.

21:41.082 --> 21:42.039
BUT SHE DIDN'T TAKE IT?

21:42.126 --> 21:43.432
SHE CHANGED HER MIND.

21:43.519 --> 21:45.391
SAID SHE WANTED YOU
TO HAVE IT.

21:47.697 --> 21:49.308
WHAT ABOUT MY MOM?
DID YOU EVER --

21:49.395 --> 21:50.874
NO.

21:50.961 --> 21:53.616
I HAVEN'T SEEN OR HEARD
FROM HER -- OR YOUR FATHER --

21:53.703 --> 21:54.965
IT'S BEEN YEARS.

21:56.663 --> 21:59.405
I HAVE TO ADMIT
I'M CURIOUS.

21:59.492 --> 22:01.537
WHAT IS IN THERE
THAT'S SO SPECIAL?

22:01.624 --> 22:04.148
SOMETHING I TOOK TRYING
TO GET BACK A LIFE I LOST,

22:04.235 --> 22:06.150
AND IT'S BEEN CHASING ME
EVER SINCE.

22:06.237 --> 22:08.936
BETTER NOT
LET IT CATCH YOU.

22:09.023 --> 22:11.765
LISTEN --
COMING HERE, I'M SORRY.

22:11.852 --> 22:15.595
THE FBI IS GONNA SHOW UP.
THEY'LL ASK QUESTIONS.

22:15.682 --> 22:19.468
THIS ISLAND WAS GETTING
A LITTLE SMALL FOR ME ANYWAY.

22:19.555 --> 22:22.906
[ CHUCKLES ]
NOW, GO.

22:22.993 --> 22:23.951
THANK YOU.

22:26.562 --> 22:28.956
FOR EVERYTHING.

22:37.399 --> 22:40.054
DO I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT'S IN THERE?

22:40.141 --> 22:43.405
PLAUSIBLE DENIABILITY.

22:43.492 --> 22:45.625
COME ON,
LET'S CATCH THAT TRAM.

22:45.712 --> 22:48.279
MY CAR'S ON
THE OTHER SIDE.

23:03.033 --> 23:04.383
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

23:06.646 --> 23:09.431
WHO IS E. PARKER?

23:09.518 --> 23:12.695
I'VE NEVER
TOLD ANYONE THIS --

23:12.782 --> 23:14.044
NOT EVEN MOZ.

23:14.131 --> 23:16.351
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

23:18.527 --> 23:20.007
YOU GONNA GET THAT?

23:22.270 --> 23:23.271
[ BEEP ]

23:23.358 --> 23:24.794
DIANA:
Peter, it's Diana.

23:24.881 --> 23:26.013
HEY.

23:26.100 --> 23:29.146
I'M WITH KRAMER.

23:29.233 --> 23:31.192
HE KNOWS CAFFREY'S
ON ROOSEVELT ISLAND.

23:31.279 --> 23:32.541
WHERE ARE YOU?

23:32.628 --> 23:34.717
WE'RE AT THE TRAM TERMINAL,
MANHATTAN SIDE.

23:34.804 --> 23:35.892
DAMN IT.

23:35.979 --> 23:37.024
WHAT'S GOING ON?

23:37.111 --> 23:38.286
You're with Caffrey.

23:38.373 --> 23:40.984
YEAH. AND WE'RE HEADED
RIGHT TO YOU.

23:51.647 --> 23:53.693
LET ME FIRST SAY
THAT AGENT BURKE AND I

23:53.780 --> 23:55.738
HAVE BEEN MARRIED
FOR 12 YEARS.

23:55.825 --> 23:57.653
IT'S A PARTNERSHIP
THAT'S BUILT ON RESPECT,

23:57.740 --> 23:58.872
ADMIRATION, AND TRUST.

23:58.959 --> 24:00.961
AND HOW IS THIS
RELEVANT?

24:01.048 --> 24:02.571
PETER'S RELATIONSHIP
WITH NEAL

24:02.658 --> 24:04.225
IS BASED ON
THE SAME ELEMENTS.

24:04.312 --> 24:05.661
YOUR HUSBAND
TRUSTS NEAL?

24:05.748 --> 24:07.924
HE DOES.
WHEN IT COUNTS.

24:08.011 --> 24:09.665
WHEN IT COUNTS?

24:09.752 --> 24:11.362
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL, NEAL WASA CON MAN.

24:11.450 --> 24:13.234
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'D WANT HIM
DATING YOUR SISTER.

24:14.583 --> 24:16.063
CAN I TAKE THAT BACK?

24:16.150 --> 24:18.413
NO.

24:18.500 --> 24:20.981
LISTEN --
PETER AND NEAL TOGETHER,

24:21.068 --> 24:22.896
THEY ARGUE AND BICKER.

24:22.983 --> 24:25.942
BUT IN THE END --
WHEN IT COUNTS --

24:26.029 --> 24:29.685
PETER PUTS UP WITH NEAL
BECAUSE HE'S WORTH IT.

24:29.772 --> 24:32.993
SHOULD MR. CAFFREY'S SENTENCE
BE COMMUTED?

24:33.080 --> 24:34.951
YES.

24:35.038 --> 24:36.692
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

24:36.779 --> 24:38.433
THIS IS NOTGOOD.

24:38.520 --> 24:40.653
NO, WE RIDE THIS OUT,

24:40.740 --> 24:42.306
AND YOU'RE PUT AWAY
FOR 20 YEARS.

24:42.393 --> 24:43.873
WELL, MAYBE
THERE'S ANOTHER WAY.

24:43.960 --> 24:45.614
WHAT?

24:45.701 --> 24:47.050
NO. FORGET THAT.

24:47.137 --> 24:48.443
YOU'LL NEVER SURVIVE
THE FALL.

24:48.530 --> 24:49.662
I'M NOT GONNA TO JUMP.

24:49.749 --> 24:50.793
THEN WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU PLANNING?

24:50.880 --> 24:52.708
HELP ME OUT
AND I'LL TELL YOU.

24:52.795 --> 24:54.362
NO, TELL ME,
THENI'LL HELP YOU OUT.

24:54.449 --> 24:56.190
YOU FIRST.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

24:56.277 --> 24:57.321
FINE.

24:57.408 --> 24:59.933
[ GRUNTS ]

25:03.632 --> 25:04.720
THANK YOU.

25:04.807 --> 25:06.069
AND?

25:06.156 --> 25:07.941
AND I'M DOUBLING BACK
TOWARD ROOSEVELT ISLAND.

25:08.028 --> 25:09.072
WISH ME LUCK.

25:09.159 --> 25:11.771
WHAT? NO.
NEAL, THAT'S CRAZY.

25:14.600 --> 25:16.863
DAMN IT,
GET BACK IN HERE!

25:16.950 --> 25:18.168
NEAL!

25:19.909 --> 25:21.520
YOU'LL NEVER MAKE IT!

25:23.391 --> 25:24.348
NEAL!

25:27.787 --> 25:29.136
NEAL!

25:39.320 --> 25:42.323
WOW.

25:46.675 --> 25:48.155
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

25:50.026 --> 25:51.811
WHAT'S UP, MOZ?

25:51.898 --> 25:53.464
NEAL,
YOU GOT A SECOND?

25:53.552 --> 25:54.553
I do now.

25:54.640 --> 25:56.076
IT SOUNDS WINDY
WHERE YOU ARE.

25:56.163 --> 25:57.730
YEAH. WHAT IS IT?

25:57.817 --> 25:59.079
SARA AND I
HAVE A PLAN.

25:59.166 --> 26:00.646
ARE YOU STILL
ON ROOSEVELT ISLAND?

26:00.733 --> 26:01.777
I WILL BE SOON.

26:01.864 --> 26:04.040
I've carved out
an escape route.

26:04.127 --> 26:05.433
MEET ME
AT THE TRAFFIC CIRCLE

26:05.520 --> 26:07.391
WHERE ROAD 5
AND EAST ROAD CONNECT.

26:07.478 --> 26:09.829
I'M ON MY WAY.

26:24.495 --> 26:26.715
YOU GONNA TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED UP THERE?

26:26.802 --> 26:28.412
I TRACKED NEAL
TO THE ISLAND.

26:28.499 --> 26:29.936
I WAS
BRINGING HIM BACK --

26:30.023 --> 26:31.938
THEN WHERE IS HE?HE'D BE HERE WITH ME NOW

26:32.025 --> 26:34.027
IF YOU HADN'T THROWN
A DOZEN GUNS AT HIS FACE.

26:34.114 --> 26:35.550
THIS IS MYFAULT?

26:35.637 --> 26:37.857
YOU BOX HIM IN,
HE'S GONNA RUN.

26:37.944 --> 26:40.207
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW TO HANDLE HIM.

26:40.294 --> 26:41.425
IDO.

26:41.512 --> 26:43.340
[ CHUCKLES ]
CLEARLY.

26:43.427 --> 26:45.342
TELL ME, PETE.

26:45.429 --> 26:46.779
NEAL HAVE THE PAINTING
ON HIM?

26:46.866 --> 26:49.608
NOT THAT I SAW.

26:49.695 --> 26:53.481
ARE YOU HANDLING HIM
OR BECOMINGHIM?

26:53.568 --> 26:56.963
SIR. THE EASTBOUND TRAM
IS APPROACHING THE ISLAND.

26:57.050 --> 27:00.836
MAINTAIN PURSUIT ON CAFFREY.
I'M HEADING DOWNTOWN.

27:00.923 --> 27:02.446
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

27:02.533 --> 27:05.101
NEAL'S GOT UNDER AN HOUR
TO MEET SARA ELLIS.

27:05.188 --> 27:07.451
IF HE MAKES IT,
I'LL BE WAITING FOR HIM.

27:07.538 --> 27:09.889
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

27:11.717 --> 27:13.109
Man: RIGHT NOW.

27:13.196 --> 27:16.069
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

27:16.156 --> 27:18.724
Woman: COMING IN NOW.MOM, LOOK AT THAT.

27:23.772 --> 27:25.121
NEAL?

27:27.471 --> 27:29.169
MOZ, START THE ENGINE!

27:29.256 --> 27:30.474
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

27:30.561 --> 27:32.346
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

27:39.135 --> 27:41.094
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

27:47.187 --> 27:51.104
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]

27:56.544 --> 27:58.198
CAFFREY UNDERSTANDS PEOPLE.

27:58.285 --> 28:00.809
YOU NEED SPACE,
HE KEEPS TO HIMSELF.

28:00.896 --> 28:02.724
YOU NEED TO TALK,
HE LISTENS.

28:02.811 --> 28:04.857
YOU NEED A BEER,
HE'LL POUR.

28:04.944 --> 28:07.729
[ CHUCKLES ] ALTHOUGH HE'LL LET
YOU KNOW HE'S SLUMMING IT.

28:07.816 --> 28:10.166
DO YOU SUPPORT
HIS COMMUTATION?

28:10.253 --> 28:13.126
HE'S DAMN GOOD
AT WHAT HE DOES,

28:13.213 --> 28:15.781
AND I CONSIDER HIM
A FRIEND.

28:17.391 --> 28:19.175
BUT THAT DOESN'T CHANGE
THE FACT

28:19.262 --> 28:21.090
THAT HE'S A CONVICTED
BOND FORGER

28:21.177 --> 28:23.658
AND PRISON ESCAPEE.

28:23.745 --> 28:26.661
I THINK HE SHOULD FINISH OUT
HIS TWO YEARS WITH THE BUREAU

28:26.748 --> 28:28.619
AND BE GRATEFUL...

28:28.707 --> 28:31.492
THAT HE'S GOT THE BEST DAMN DEAL
I'VE EVER SEEN.

28:36.932 --> 28:38.760
OKAY, SARA'S WAITING FOR YOU
AT STERLING BOSCH.

28:38.847 --> 28:40.806
IF YOU CAN MAKE THE HAND-OFF
IN TIME, YOU'RE GOLDEN.

28:40.893 --> 28:42.242
"IF."

28:42.329 --> 28:43.983
WELL, THE ODDS OF YOU
MAKING IT ARE --

28:44.070 --> 28:45.549
I KNOW, MOZ.

28:45.636 --> 28:47.160
BUT I DON'T HAVE
A CHOICE.
YES.

28:47.247 --> 28:48.683
YOU DO.

28:52.382 --> 28:53.862
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

28:53.949 --> 28:55.734
WHAT'S LOLANA DOING HERE?

28:55.821 --> 28:58.127
WELL, DURING OUR BRIEF
ALIENATION --

28:58.214 --> 29:01.217
BEFORE THE WHOLE
KELLER FIASCO...

29:03.916 --> 29:05.613
...I MOVED YOUR PORTION OF
THE TREASURE OUT OF THE COUNTRY,

29:05.700 --> 29:07.789
SHOULD YOU EVER CARE
TO CLAIM IT.

29:07.876 --> 29:09.617
YOU SAVED MY HALF?

29:09.704 --> 29:10.836
WELL, A LITTLE LESS
THAN HALF.

29:12.098 --> 29:14.056
I WAS ANGRY -- SUE ME.

29:14.143 --> 29:15.754
IT'S STILL WORTH MORE
THAN EITHER OF US

29:15.841 --> 29:17.190
COULD EVER SPEND
IN A LIFETIME.

29:17.277 --> 29:19.540
WE COULD RUN.
RIGHT NOW.

29:19.627 --> 29:20.846
NEVER LOOK BACK.

29:22.630 --> 29:24.806
I DON'T WANT TO RUN
ANYMORE, MOZ.

29:24.893 --> 29:26.808
Dispatcher: ALL UNITS, BE ON THE LOOKOUT

29:26.895 --> 29:28.854
FOR STOLEN AMBULANCE 313.

29:28.941 --> 29:31.639
THAT'S US.
SO MUCH FOR NOT RUNNING.

29:31.726 --> 29:33.859
I HAVE TO FINISH THIS.

29:33.946 --> 29:37.558
I SOMEHOW KNEW
YOU WERE GONNA SAY THAT.

29:37.645 --> 29:39.734
BUT FOR LOLANA'S SAKE,
I HAD TO GIVE IT A TRY.

29:39.821 --> 29:41.562
GO.

29:41.649 --> 29:42.955
I'LL LEAD
THE FEDERAL BLOODHOUNDS

29:43.042 --> 29:44.608
ON A CHASE OF
THE WILD-GOOSE VARIETY.

29:44.695 --> 29:47.220
THANKS, MOZ.

29:47.307 --> 29:48.830
HERE.

29:48.917 --> 29:50.527
IF I DON'T MAKE IT,
YOU AND LOLANA WILL NEED THAT

29:50.614 --> 29:51.877
TO GET TO THE ISLAND
WITHOUT ME.

29:53.966 --> 29:55.489
YOU'LL MAKE IT.

29:55.576 --> 29:57.360
[ SLAPS DOOR LIGHTLY ]

30:00.233 --> 30:03.062
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

30:06.500 --> 30:08.197
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]HEY, SARA.

30:08.284 --> 30:09.329
WHERE ARE YOU?

30:09.416 --> 30:10.983
A FEW BLOCKS AWAY.

30:11.070 --> 30:13.289
LISTEN -- MEET ME IN THE LOBBY.
IT'S GONNA BE CLOSE.

30:13.376 --> 30:15.683
NEAL, I --
[ SIGHS ]

30:15.770 --> 30:17.772
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ][ SIGHS ]

30:17.859 --> 30:19.861
NEAL.

30:19.948 --> 30:21.428
SARA,
HAVE YOU HEARD FROM NEAL?

30:21.515 --> 30:22.603
HE'S GOT THE PAINTING,

30:22.690 --> 30:24.126
BUT HE'S NOT GONNA
GET PAST KRAMER.

30:24.213 --> 30:26.607
He may not have to.

30:26.694 --> 30:28.130
GET US A MEETING WITH YOUR BOSS
IN THE NEXT FIVE MINUTES.

30:28.217 --> 30:30.089
I'LL TRY.Don't try. Do it.

30:30.176 --> 30:32.091
[ BEEP ]

30:35.355 --> 30:37.183
I HAVE EYES ON CAFFREY.

30:37.270 --> 30:38.924
NOT GOOD.

30:39.011 --> 30:39.925
HEADING EAST ON PEARL.

30:42.797 --> 30:44.668
OH,
I'M GONNA REGRET THIS.

30:45.800 --> 30:48.411
[ BEEPING ]

30:48.498 --> 30:51.850
WHAT?! HEY! HEY!
YOU GOT TO MOVE THAT THING!

30:51.937 --> 30:54.287
NO CAN DO, MA'AM.

30:59.335 --> 31:01.642
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

31:01.729 --> 31:02.861
WHOA!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

31:02.948 --> 31:04.340
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!
HEY!

31:18.877 --> 31:20.443
[ TIRES SCREECH ]NEAL!

31:20.530 --> 31:22.445
GET IN!

31:27.407 --> 31:29.888
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

31:29.975 --> 31:32.368
WOMAN: Agent Kramer,
we lost Caffrey.

31:32.455 --> 31:34.327
Kramer: ALL UNITS FALL BACK
TO STERLING BOSCH.

31:34.414 --> 31:37.721
FORM A PERIMETER
AROUND THE BUILDING.

31:37.808 --> 31:39.636
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

31:39.723 --> 31:41.334
THANK YOU.GOOD LUCK, CAFFREY.

31:46.774 --> 31:49.081
YOUR PROPOSAL...

31:49.168 --> 31:51.126
IT ALL SEEMS
HIGHLY IRREGULAR.

31:51.213 --> 31:52.301
YES, MR. BOSCH,

31:52.388 --> 31:54.477
BUT YOU CAN ADMIT
THAT IRREGULARITY

31:54.564 --> 31:56.218
HAS WORKED VERYWELL FOR ME
IN THE PAST.

31:56.305 --> 31:57.916
AND I'M OFFERING YOU
AN OPPORTUNITY

31:58.003 --> 32:00.614
TO MAKE $15 MILLION
IN FIVE MINUTES.

32:00.701 --> 32:04.313
AGENT BURKE, YOU CAN ASSURE ME
THIS IS ALL LEGAL?

32:04.400 --> 32:07.012
I WOULDN'T BE HERE
IF IT WEREN'T.

32:07.099 --> 32:08.927
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO?

32:09.014 --> 32:11.930
JUST SIGN
SOME START PAPERWORK, SIR.

32:24.507 --> 32:26.901
I'D SAY THIS MOMENT
WAS INEVITABLE,

32:26.988 --> 32:29.077
WOULDN'T YOU, NEAL?

32:29.164 --> 32:31.645
I KNEW YOU COULD BE
REASONABLE.

32:31.732 --> 32:35.605
I THINK YOU MIGHT TAKE
A REAL SHINE TO D.C. AFTER ALL.

32:36.911 --> 32:37.956
DON'T COUNT ON IT.

32:40.088 --> 32:42.047
AH, YOU DO THE HONORS,
PETE.

32:47.530 --> 32:50.664
I should have listened to you.
I played right into his hands.

32:50.751 --> 32:52.840
It's not over yet.

32:52.927 --> 32:55.364
RAPHAEL'S SAINT GEORGE AND THE DRAGON.

32:55.451 --> 32:56.496
A SEMINAL WORK.

32:56.583 --> 32:58.193
Sara: EXCUSE ME.

32:58.280 --> 33:00.848
THAT PAINTING IS PROPERTY
OF STERLING BOSCH INSURANCE.

33:00.935 --> 33:03.633
[ CHUCKLES ]
VALIANT EFFORT, MS. ELLIS.

33:03.720 --> 33:07.333
THIS IS EVIDENCE
IN A CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION.

33:07.420 --> 33:08.856
INVESTIGATION INTO WHAT?

33:08.943 --> 33:10.989
CLASS "B" POSSESSION
OF STOLEN PROPERTY.

33:11.076 --> 33:12.425
AND YOU ARE?

33:12.512 --> 33:15.558
WINSTON BOSCH.
THIS YOUNG LADY WORKS FOR ME.

33:15.645 --> 33:17.996
I DON'T SEE ANYONE HERE
WITH STOLEN PROPERTY.

33:18.083 --> 33:19.432
THIS PAINTING --

33:19.519 --> 33:21.129
BELONGS TO
STERLING BOSCH.

33:21.216 --> 33:23.827
WE HIRED MR. CAFFREY
TO AUTHENTICATE IT FOR US.

33:23.914 --> 33:25.568
THE HELL YOU DID.

33:25.655 --> 33:27.788
YES. IDID. HERE.

33:27.875 --> 33:31.096
MR. CAFFREY IS QUITE
THE ART EXPERT.

33:31.183 --> 33:34.055
HE'S EVEN WORKED FOR THE FBI
AS AN AUTHENTICATOR.

33:34.142 --> 33:35.100
I CAN ATTEST TO THAT.

33:35.187 --> 33:36.840
AND IF HE'S GOOD ENOUGH
FOR YOU,

33:36.927 --> 33:38.538
HE'S GOOD ENOUGH FOR ME.

33:38.625 --> 33:39.669
YOU'RE PART OF THIS?

33:39.756 --> 33:41.323
WELL, MR. CAFFREY,

33:41.410 --> 33:44.152
WHAT'S YOUR PROFESSIONAL
ASSESSMENT OF THIS PIECE?

33:44.239 --> 33:48.635
OH, THAT IS DEFINITELY
THE REAL RAPHAEL.

33:48.722 --> 33:51.942
I'D STAKE MY REPUTATION
ON IT.

33:52.030 --> 33:53.161
EXCELLENT.

33:53.248 --> 33:55.250
AND FOR YOUR SERVICES --
$1,200.

33:55.337 --> 33:57.731
SORRY. NEAL'S NOT ALLOWED
TO ACCEPT PAYMENT

33:57.818 --> 33:59.385
WHILE HE WORKS FOR US.
OH?

33:59.472 --> 34:00.995
EVEN BETTER.

34:03.171 --> 34:05.826
SEE YOU AROUND, CAFFREY.SEE YOU AROUND.

34:08.916 --> 34:11.179
[ SIGHS ]
WHY DON'T YOU HEAD HOME?

34:11.266 --> 34:13.877
GET SOME REST.
GOT A BIG DAY TOMORROW.

34:13.964 --> 34:15.401
YOU GONNA BE OKAY?

34:15.488 --> 34:18.491
I'LL BE FINE. GO.

34:21.059 --> 34:23.409
YOU WENT BEHIND MY BACK,

34:23.496 --> 34:25.889
CONSPIRED TO
OBSTRUCT JUSTICE.

34:25.976 --> 34:27.456
I COULD SAY
YOU DID THE SAME.

34:27.543 --> 34:29.110
WAKE UP, PETEY!
OPEN YOUR EYES!

34:29.197 --> 34:31.199
YOU'RE NOT HIS PARTNER.
YOU'RE HIS MARK!

34:31.286 --> 34:32.635
THIS BOY'S RUN
SUCH A GOOD CONFIDENCE GAME,

34:32.722 --> 34:33.854
HE'S GOT YOU THINKING

34:33.941 --> 34:35.421
THAT YOU'VE COME OUT AHEAD
IN ALL THIS.

34:35.508 --> 34:38.163
WHEN DID YOU STOP PUTTING FAITH
IN PEOPLE?

34:38.250 --> 34:39.947
WHEN THEY STOPPED
DESERVING IT.

34:40.034 --> 34:41.209
OH.

34:43.037 --> 34:46.301
THIS ISN'T OVER YET, PETE.

34:46.388 --> 34:47.868
NOT BY A LONG SHOT.

34:57.051 --> 35:01.229
MR. CAFFREY,
DO YOU DESERVE TO BE FREE?

35:01.316 --> 35:04.014
THAT'S NOT FOR ME
TO DECIDE.

35:06.016 --> 35:07.975
I WON'T SIT HERE
AND GIVE YOU SOME MONOLOGUE

35:08.062 --> 35:10.064
ABOUT HOW REFORMED I AM.

35:10.151 --> 35:12.371
ACTIONS SPEAK LOUDER
THAN WORDS,

35:12.458 --> 35:15.548
AND, HOPEFULLY, MY ACTIONS
WHILE IN SERVICE TO THE FBI

35:15.635 --> 35:17.027
SAY MORE THAN I CAN.

35:17.115 --> 35:20.509
AND WHAT WOULD YOU DO
WITH YOUR FREEDOM?

35:20.596 --> 35:22.990
WELL, I CAN
TELL YOU ONE THING.

35:23.077 --> 35:25.775
I WON'T BE GOING ANYWHERE
ANYTIME SOON.

35:25.862 --> 35:27.734
YOU WON'T?
NO.

35:27.821 --> 35:29.562
I'M HAPPY HERE.

35:29.649 --> 35:31.955
YOU KNOW,
SOMEONE ONCE TOLD ME

35:32.042 --> 35:37.004
MY LIFE IS A DREAM
WITH AN ANKLET ATTACHED.

35:37.091 --> 35:39.963
IF I WAKE UP TOMORROW
AND THAT ANKLET IS STILL ON --

35:40.050 --> 35:44.577
I HAVE A GOOD JOB,
A WONDERFUL HOME...

35:44.664 --> 35:47.754
A PARTNER
AND A BEST FRIEND.

35:49.582 --> 35:51.410
A FAMILY.

35:54.369 --> 35:58.765
BUT TO WAKE UP
AND ANSWER ONLY TO MYSELF...

36:02.160 --> 36:04.162
...THAT WOULD MEAN
EVERYTHING.

36:05.641 --> 36:08.296
WE HAVE ONE MORE INTERVIEW
TO CONDUCT

36:08.383 --> 36:09.993
BEFORE WE MAKE
OUR DECISION.

36:10.080 --> 36:12.126
YOU'LL HAVE AN ANSWER HERE TODAY
BY 5:00 P.M.

36:12.213 --> 36:13.606
THANK YOU.

36:15.521 --> 36:17.305
HEY.

36:17.392 --> 36:19.133
HOW'D IT GO?

36:19.220 --> 36:21.657
AS WELL AS IT COULDGO,
I THINK.

36:21.744 --> 36:24.138
YOU KNOW
WHAT THE NICE THING IS?

36:24.225 --> 36:25.618
HMM?

36:25.705 --> 36:27.185
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

36:27.272 --> 36:28.708
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

36:28.795 --> 36:30.840
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA GO IN THERE
AND SAY YOUR PIECE,

36:30.927 --> 36:32.668
AND THE BOARD'S GONNA MAKE
THEIR DECISION.

36:32.755 --> 36:34.757
BUT WITH OR WITHOUT
MY ANKLET,

36:34.844 --> 36:37.195
COME MONDAY MORNING,
I'M GONNA STEP OFF THAT ELEVATOR

36:37.282 --> 36:38.892
ON THE 21st FLOOR
AND GO TO WORK.

36:41.721 --> 36:44.071
YOU ONCE TOLD ME
YOU NEVER LIED TO ME

36:44.158 --> 36:45.464
AND YOU NEVER WILL.

36:45.551 --> 36:48.902
SO I NEED TO KNOW
SOMETHING.

36:48.989 --> 36:52.427
THE FIRST TIME KRAMER AND I
WENT AFTER YOU FOR THE DEGAS,

36:52.514 --> 36:54.473
HOW'D YOU SWITCH
THE PAINTINGS?

36:58.085 --> 37:00.305
I SNUCK UP TO THE PENTHOUSE,
PULLED THE SWAP,

37:00.392 --> 37:02.132
THEN BASE-JUMPED
OFF THE BUILDING

37:02.220 --> 37:03.438
AND LANDED
ON WALL STREET.

37:03.525 --> 37:05.658
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:05.745 --> 37:07.442
FINE. DON'TTELL ME.

37:09.531 --> 37:12.360
I GOT TO GO IN.

37:14.884 --> 37:17.147
THAT PERSON YOU SAW
ON ROOSEVELT ISLAND --

37:17.235 --> 37:18.584
WHO WAS IT?

37:21.195 --> 37:23.676
WHEN THIS IS OVER...

37:23.763 --> 37:25.591
I'LL TELL YOU EVERYTHING.

37:28.028 --> 37:29.899
SEE YOU SOON.

37:56.491 --> 37:58.928
THEY'RE READY FOR YOU NOW,
AGENT BURKE.

37:59.015 --> 38:01.844
THANKS, HENRY.

38:01.931 --> 38:03.716
WHAT IS THIS?

38:03.803 --> 38:05.283
THESE MARSHALS ARE HERE
TO TAKE NEAL CAFFREY

38:05.370 --> 38:06.762
INTO CUSTODY
WHEN HE RETURNS.

38:06.849 --> 38:08.547
FOR WHAT?

38:08.634 --> 38:10.157
IF YOU HAD ONLY LISTENED
TO ME.

38:10.244 --> 38:12.638
FOR WHAT?PUBLIC ENDANGERMENT.

38:12.725 --> 38:14.770
I'VE GOT A DOZEN
EYEWITNESSES

38:14.857 --> 38:16.946
WHO SAW CAFFREY
HOP THAT TRAM.

38:17.033 --> 38:18.992
COMBINE THAT
WITH EVADING ARREST,

38:19.079 --> 38:20.515
OBSTRUCTION OF JUSTICE.

38:20.602 --> 38:22.952
HELL, I MAY EVEN THROW IN
A JAYWALKING CHARGE

38:23.039 --> 38:24.171
FOR GOOD MEASURE.

38:24.258 --> 38:26.260
WE'RE NOT IN
THE REVENGE BUSINESS.

38:26.347 --> 38:28.828
NEAL PISSED YOU OFF,
AND NOW YOU WANT TO HURT HIM.

38:28.915 --> 38:29.916
JUST CONTROL HIM.

38:30.003 --> 38:32.179
NEAL'S GOT A LOT
OF SKELETONS.

38:32.266 --> 38:34.616
I'LL PICK ONE,
SLAP THAT ANKLET ON HIM,

38:34.703 --> 38:37.010
AND HE'LL WORK FOR ME
IN D.C. PERMANENTLY.

38:39.099 --> 38:43.103
YOU UNDERSTAND THIS IS BEST
FOR EVERYONE, DON'T YOU?

38:56.725 --> 38:58.423
DON'T YOU?

39:01.861 --> 39:03.602
I HAVE A STATEMENT
TO MAKE.

39:06.996 --> 39:09.216
STATE YOUR NAME AND RELATIONSHIP
TO NEAL CAFFREY

39:09.303 --> 39:10.435
FOR THE RECORD, PLEASE.

39:10.522 --> 39:12.088
SPECIAL AGENT PETER BURKE.

39:12.175 --> 39:14.090
I'VE BEEN
NEAL CAFFREY'S HANDLER

39:14.177 --> 39:16.397
AT THE FEDERAL BUREAU
OF INVESTIGATION

39:16.484 --> 39:18.486
SINCE HIS RELEASE
INTO OUR CUSTODY.

39:18.573 --> 39:19.792
YOUCAUGHT HIM?

39:19.879 --> 39:21.228
TWICE.

39:21.315 --> 39:24.623
AND YOU SHOULD KNOW,
THE LAST TIME I CAUGHT HIM,

39:24.710 --> 39:26.929
HE WAS SITTING ALONE
IN AN EMPTY APARTMENT.

39:27.016 --> 39:28.801
HE HAD NOTHING.
NO ONE.

39:28.888 --> 39:30.106
AND NOW?

39:30.193 --> 39:33.153
HE HAS A LIFE.
A REAL LIFE HERE.

39:33.240 --> 39:36.069
ONE THAT KEEPS HIM GROUNDED
AND DECENT.

39:36.156 --> 39:37.418
AS YOU'VE HEARD,

39:37.505 --> 39:39.507
THERE ARE MANY PEOPLE
WHO CARE ABOUT NEAL,

39:39.594 --> 39:42.510
PEOPLE WHO SEE HIM
AS MORE THAN JUST A CRIMINAL.

39:42.597 --> 39:44.512
HE'S FRUSTRATING,
I'LL ADMIT.

39:44.599 --> 39:46.862
HE DRIVES ME CRAZY
ON HIS BEST DAYS.

39:46.949 --> 39:48.429
I DON'T ALWAYS HAVE TO KNOW
WHERE NEAL IS

39:48.516 --> 39:49.691
OR WHAT HE'S UP TO.

39:49.778 --> 39:53.521
BUT I DO KNOW
THAT HE HAS A GOOD HEART

39:53.608 --> 39:56.219
AND A SET OF PRINCIPLES...[ BEEPING ]

39:56.306 --> 39:57.656
...THAT WEREN'T THERE
SIX YEARS AGO

39:57.743 --> 39:59.266
WHEN HE WAS JUST
ANOTHER CASE FILE

39:59.353 --> 40:00.659
THAT GOT DROPPED
ON MY DESK.

40:00.746 --> 40:05.403
DO YOU THINK
MR. CAFFREY IS REFORMED?

40:05.490 --> 40:08.493
AS LONG AS HE'S ON THAT ANKLET,
WE'LL NEVER KNOW.

40:08.580 --> 40:10.669
WE CAN SIT HERE
UNTIL KINGDOM COME

40:10.756 --> 40:13.062
AND DEBATE OVER
WHO IS NEAL CAFFREY.

40:13.149 --> 40:15.238
BUT AS LONG
AS WE KEEP HIM TETHERED,

40:15.325 --> 40:17.502
AS LONG AS WE TREAT HIM
LIKE A CRIMINAL,

40:17.589 --> 40:21.331
HE'LL ALWAYS THINK
THAT HE IS ONE.

40:21.419 --> 40:25.858
WHETHER NEAL IS A CITIZEN,
A C.I., OR A THIEF

40:25.945 --> 40:29.862
IS A DECISION THAT NEEDS
TO BE PUT IN HIS HANDS.

40:29.949 --> 40:31.385
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]AGENT BURKE...

40:31.472 --> 40:35.215
HELLO?...SHOULD NEAL CAFFREY'S
SENTENCE BE COMMUTED?

40:41.569 --> 40:43.484
YES.

40:43.571 --> 40:47.357
I'M SAYING NEAL
SHOULD BE FREE.

40:47.445 --> 40:49.229
I'M SORRY --
THIS COULDN'T WAIT.

40:49.316 --> 40:51.492
PETER, CAFFREY'S
CUT HIS ANKLET.

40:51.579 --> 40:53.668
NEAL'S GONE.
